To style a button with a bright green background and white text, you can use the following CSS code:

```
button {
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

Here's a breakdown of the code:

- `button` selector targets all buttons on the page.
- `background-color: green;` sets the background color of the button to bright green.
- `color: white;` sets the text color of the button to white.
- `padding: 10px 20px;` adds some space between the button's content and its border.
- `border: none;` removes the button's border.
- `border-radius: 5px;` adds rounded corners to the button.
- `cursor: pointer;` changes the cursor of the button to a pointer when it's hovered over.

You can customize the code to fit your specific needs, such as changing the button's size or adding a hover effect.
